As Neil wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/25/2004 at 05:45:10 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>Dear Sir,
>
>I am looking for the formula for the volume of a Sperical cap when 
>one knows the contact angle between the sphere and the plane and the 
>radius of the circle in the plane (r1 on your spherical cap page).
>
>[Difficulty]
>When attempting to substitute for r and h I seem to be making an 
>error, resulting in unrealistic answers.
>
>[Thoughts]
>

Hello Neil,

See the diagram at

http://mathforum.org/dr.math/gifs/sphcap.jpg

Is the "contact angle" you refer to the angle t in the diagram?

cos(pi/2 -t) = r1/r

or

sin(t) = r1/r.

You can write the formula

V=(pi/6)(3r1^2+h^2)*h

in terms of t if you wish.

- Doctor Jerry, The Math Forum
  <http://mathforum.org/dr.math/>
